# Cursor Rules for Ayushman Educational Academy Marketing Web

## Project Overview

This is a Next.js 16 marketing website for Ayushman Educational Academy built with:

- Next.js 16 (App Router)
- React 19
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- Tailwind CSS v4
- Lucide React (icons)

## Code Style & Conventions

### TypeScript

- Use strict TypeScript with proper type definitions
- Define explicit types for all props, state, and function parameters
- Use type aliases for reusable types (e.g., `type ButtonProps = {...}`)
- Prefer `type` over `interface` for component props
- Always use proper typing - avoid `any` unless absolutely necessary

### React Components

- Use functional components with hooks
- Use default exports for components
- Add `"use client"` directive at the top of client components
- Use descriptive component names (PascalCase)
- Keep components focused and single-purpose
- Extract reusable logic into custom hooks when appropriate

### Component Structure

```tsx
"use client";

import React, { useState } from "react";
import ComponentName from "@/components/ComponentName";

type ComponentProps = {
  prop1: string;
  prop2?: number;
};

export default function ComponentName(props: ComponentProps) {
  // Component logic
  return (
    // JSX
  );
}
```

### File Organization

- Pages: `app/**/page.tsx`
- Components: `components/ComponentName.tsx`
- Use path aliases: `@/components/...`, `@/app/...`
- One component per file
- Use descriptive file names matching component names

### Next.js App Router

- Use App Router conventions (not Pages Router)
- Use `useRouter()` from `next/navigation` for navigation
- Use `usePathname()` from `next/navigation` for pathname detection
- Use `Link` from `next/link` for client-side navigation
- Server components by default, add `"use client"` only when needed

### Styling with Tailwind CSS

- Use Tailwind utility classes exclusively
- Follow responsive design patterns: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:` breakpoints
- Use semantic color classes: `bg-blue-600`, `text-gray-700`, etc.
- Apply hover states: `hover:bg-blue-700`, `hover:scale-105`
- Use transitions: `transition`, `transition-all duration-300`
- Group related styles logically
- Use spacing utilities: `px-4`, `py-2`, `gap-6`, `mb-4`
- Use flexbox/grid utilities: `flex`, `items-center`, `justify-between`

### Component Props Pattern

- Define props as a type with descriptive names
- Use optional props with `?` when appropriate
- Destructure props in function parameters or use `props.` notation
- Include `className?: string` for style overrides
- Use `React.ReactNode` for children

### State Management

- Use `useState` for local component state
- Keep state as close to where it's used as possible
- Use descriptive state variable names (e.g., `isDialogOpen`, `isFeesDialogOpen`)

### Navigation & Routing

- Use `router.push("/path")` for programmatic navigation
- Use `Link` component for declarative navigation
- Check active routes with `usePathname()` and `pathname.startsWith(href)`

### Icons

- Import icons from `lucide-react`
- Use descriptive icon names: `ArrowRightIcon`, `MenuIcon`, `XIcon`
- Apply consistent sizing: `w-4 h-4`, `w-6 h-6`

### Code Formatting

- Use 2 spaces for indentation
- Use semicolons
- Use single quotes for strings (or double quotes - be consistent)
- Add blank lines between logical sections
- Use trailing commas in objects/arrays

### Comments

- Use section comments with emojis for visual organization: `{/* ðŸ”¹ Section Name */}`
- Add comments for complex logic
- Keep comments concise and meaningful

### Accessibility

- Use semantic HTML elements
- Add proper ARIA labels when needed
- Ensure keyboard navigation works
- Maintain proper heading hierarchy

### Performance

- Use Next.js Image component for images (when applicable)
- Lazy load components when appropriate
- Optimize bundle size by importing only needed icons

### Error Handling

- Use ErrorBoundary for error catching
- Handle loading states appropriately
- Provide user-friendly error messages

## Common Patterns

### Dialog/Modal Pattern

```tsx
{
  isDialogOpen && (
    <div className="fixed inset-0 bg-black/50 backdrop-blur-sm flex justify-center items-center z-50">
      <div className="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-xl p-8">
        {/* Content */}
        <button onClick={() => setIsDialogOpen(false)}>Close</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

